The paper discusses a web application that visualizes institutional performance within specific subject areas, using data from Scopus. The subject areas are not specified, but the paper focuses on the effect of country-specific characteristics on research performance, which suggests that the paper may be relevant to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely sub-category, as the paper discusses a web application for visualizing institutional performance. 

cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely, as the paper examines the effect of country-specific characteristics on research performance, which has implications for the social and ethical aspects of computing. 

cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering) are also possible sub-categories, as the paper uses statistical models to analyze and rank institutions based on their research performance. 

cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a less likely sub-category, but may be relevant as the paper discusses the use of statistical models to analyze data from Scopus.
